Goal
- Write a professional yet approachable email to the team explaining that the Q3 roadmap is delayed by 3 weeks due to a vendor-related issue, without assigning blame to the vendor or team members.

Context
- Audience: internal team members familiar with the Q3 roadmap.
- Tone: professional but conversational, avoiding overly corporate or stiff language.
- Content requirements:
  - Clearly communicate the 3-week delay in the Q3 roadmap.
  - Avoid blaming the vendor or any team member.
  - Mention that a mitigation plan exists but details are not finalized.
  - Specify what aspects of the roadmap are changing and which remain unchanged.

Constraints
- Use neutral, forward-looking language without assigning fault.
- Keep the email concise and clear.
- Avoid overly formal or corporate jargon.
- Do not finalize or speculate on mitigation details; only acknowledge their existence.

Output format
- Use a clear email format with greeting, body, and closing.
- Keep the email under 300 words.
- Use paragraphs and bullet points where appropriate for clarity.
- End with a polite closing and invitation for questions.

Examples
- Brief excerpt:  
  "Due to unforeseen vendor-related delays, our Q3 roadmap timeline will shift by approximately three weeks. We are actively working on a mitigation plan, which I will share once finalized. Here’s what will change and what remains on track..."

- Checklist for the email:  
  - [x] State the delay and duration clearly  
  - [x] Avoid blame language  
  - [x] Mention mitigation plan without details  
  - [x] Clarify changes vs. unchanged items  
  - [x] Maintain professional but approachable tone  

Success criteria
- The email clearly informs the team of the delay without assigning blame.
- The tone is professional yet not overly formal or stiff.
- The team understands what is changing and what remains the same.
- The email acknowledges a mitigation plan without premature details.
- The email invites team engagement or questions.

Verification
- Confirm the email meets tone and content requirements and respects constraints before sending.